{"badges":["TM5","TM6"],"preparations":[{"title":"Pavlova","content":["Preheat oven to 300°F. Line a baking sheet with parchment and set aside.","Place 6 oz sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to a bowl and set aside.","Place remaining 6 oz sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>20 sec\/speed 10<b>. Transfer to bowl with ground sugar and set aside. Clean and dry mixing bowl."," <strong>Insert butterfly whisk<\/strong>. Place egg whites and cream of tartar into mixing bowl and whisk <b>5 min\/100°F\/speed 3.5<b>.","Without measuring cup, whisk a further <b>5 min\/100°F\/speed 3.5<b> while slowly adding reserved ground sugar through hole in mixing bowl lid.","Add corn starch, vinegar and almond extract through hole in mixing bowl lid and mix <b>40 sec\/speed 3.5<b>."," <strong>Remove butterfly whisk<\/strong>. With spatula, transfer meringue mixture onto prepared baking sheet and spread out evenly into a rectangular shape. Run a skewer through the meringue to create swirls. Sprinkle almonds around edge. Bake for 10 minutes (300°F). Reduce temperature to 250°F and bake a further 60 minutes (250°F). Turn off oven and without opening oven door allow Pavlova to cool (approx. 2 hrs.). Meanwhile clean mixing bowl."]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["Place vanilla bean and sugar into mixing bowl and grind <b>10 sec\/speed 10<b>. Scrape down sides of mixing bowl with spatula.","Add liqueur and cook <b>5 min\/Varoma\/speed 2<b>. Transfer to a bowl and let cool. Once cooled, strain over a bowl through a fine sieve. Discard solids.","Just before serving, top cooled pavlova with mixed berries, drizzle with reserved sauce and serve immediately."]}],"ingredients":[{"title":"Pavlova","content":["12 oz sugar, divided","8 egg whites, room temperature","&frac18; tsp cream of tartar","2 tbsp corn starch","1 tsp white vinegar","½ tsp almond extract","1 oz sliced almonds"]},{"title":"Sauce","content":["1 vanilla bean, cut into pieces","1 oz sugar","7 oz raspberry liqueur, type Chambord","12 oz fresh mixed berries, prepared, halved or quartered"]}],"id":"r343844","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-tCwU0AcTuTQ\/XZWfpTfuXTI\/AAAAAAAAfH8\/mcdqZzL3rzcrFSHF8c9-k8MfeV--dTThACLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_zVuuORYZNOYDJr7C.png","title":"Almond Pavlova with Berries and Chambord","publishedAt":"2018-05-04T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"3 g","fat":"1 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"43 g","calories":"920 kJ \/ 220 kcal"},"usefulItems":"baking sheet, parchment paper, skewer, fine sieve, oven","hintsAndTricks":["Fat and moisture will prevent egg whites from whipping properly. Use a little vinegar to remove and clean the mixing bowl, blade and whisk. Dry thoroughly with a paper towel."],"basicInfo":["medium","15m","3h 30m","12 portions"]}